layout.p:
Columns: 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 25;
                                                  written lines: 25; Uniform layout. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Complete hard-point ruling and pricking visible. Headings and initial words in square large characters. The beginning of each pericope marked in the margin by large ornamental 'samekh'. Masorah magna generally occupies three lines at the top and four lines at the bottom of a page. A number of masoretic notes and marks at the end of each books. Centre-marks and middle verses marked. Folios 2v-3r: masoretic notes in the form of ornamental designs.
